{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":849,"text":"For the past decade,"},{"time":2344,"text":"I've been studying non-state armed groups:"},{"time":5270,"text":"armed organizations like terrorists,\ninsurgents or militias."},{"time":9588,"text":"I document what these groups do\nwhen they're not shooting."},{"time":12785,"text":"My goal is to better understand\nthese violent actors"},{"time":16372,"text":"and to study ways to encourage transition\nfrom violent engagement"},{"time":20086,"text":"to nonviolent confrontation."},{"time":21987,"text":"I work in the field, in the policy world\nand in the library."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25749,"text":"Understanding non-state armed groups\nis key to solving most ongoing conflict,"},{"time":30884,"text":"because war has changed."},{"time":32464,"text":"It used to be a contest between states."},{"time":35568,"text":"No longer."},{"time":36743,"text":"It is now a conflict between states\nand non-state actors."},{"time":41236,"text":"For example, of the 216 peace agreements"},{"time":44996,"text":"signed between 1975 and 2011,"},{"time":48430,"text":"196 of them were between a state\nand a non-state actor."},{"time":53634,"text":"So we need to understand these groups;\nwe need to either engage them"},{"time":56895,"text":"or defeat them in any conflict resolution\nprocess that has to be successful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61808,"text":"So how do we do that?"},{"time":63805,"text":"We need to know what makes\nthese organizations tick."},{"time":67148,"text":"We know a lot about\nhow they fight, why they fight,"},{"time":69965,"text":"but no one looks at what they're doing\nwhen they're not fighting."},{"time":73043,"text":"Yet, armed struggle\nand unarmed politics are related."},{"time":76659,"text":"It is all part of the same organization."},{"time":78981,"text":"We cannot understand these groups,\nlet alone defeat them,"},{"time":82162,"text":"if we don't have the full picture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":85140,"text":"And armed groups today\nare complex organizations."},{"time":88222,"text":"Take the Lebanese Hezbollah,"},{"time":90149,"text":"known for its violent\nconfrontation against Israel."},{"time":92956,"text":"But since its creation in the early 1980s,"},{"time":95815,"text":"Hezbollah has also set up\na political party,"},{"time":98424,"text":"a social-service network,\nand a military apparatus."},{"time":101765,"text":"Similarly, the Palestinian Hamas,"},{"time":104415,"text":"known for its suicide attacks\nagainst Israel,"},{"time":107006,"text":"also runs the Gaza Strip since 2007."},{"time":110234,"text":"So these groups do way more\nthan just shoot."},{"time":113453,"text":"They multi-task."},{"time":115239,"text":"They set up complex\ncommunication machines --"},{"time":118278,"text":"radio stations, TV channels,"},{"time":120445,"text":"Internet websites\nand social media strategies."},{"time":123422,"text":"And up here, you have the ISIS magazine,"},{"time":125738,"text":"printed in English\nand published to recruit."},{"time":129259,"text":"Armed groups also invest\nin complex fund-raising --"},{"time":132190,"text":"not looting, but setting up\nprofitable businesses;"},{"time":136077,"text":"for example, construction companies."},{"time":138491,"text":"Now, these activities are keys."},{"time":140398,"text":"They allow these groups\nto increase their strength,"},{"time":142842,"text":"increase their funds,"},{"time":144221,"text":"to better recruit\nand to build their brand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147537,"text":"Armed groups also do something else:"},{"time":149300,"text":"they build stronger bonds\nwith the population"},{"time":151984,"text":"by investing in social services."},{"time":154457,"text":"They build schools, they run hospitals,"},{"time":157324,"text":"they set up vocational-training programs\nor micro-loan programs."},{"time":161104,"text":"Hezbollah offers all\nof these services and more."},{"time":164905,"text":"Armed groups also seek\nto win the population over"},{"time":167738,"text":"by offering something\nthat the state is not providing:"},{"time":171662,"text":"safety and security."},{"time":174141,"text":"The initial rise of the Taliban\nin war-torn Afghanistan,"},{"time":178125,"text":"or even the beginning\nof the ascent of ISIS,"},{"time":181026,"text":"can be understood also by looking\nat these groups' efforts"},{"time":184108,"text":"to provide security."},{"time":186348,"text":"Now, unfortunately, in these cases,"},{"time":188643,"text":"the provision of security\ncame at an unbearably high price"},{"time":191913,"text":"for the population."},{"time":193347,"text":"But in general, providing\nsocial services fills a gap,"},{"time":197612,"text":"a governance gap left by the government,"},{"time":199897,"text":"and allows these groups\nto increase their strength"},{"time":202516,"text":"and their power."},{"time":204040,"text":"For example, the 2006 electoral victory\nof the Palestinian Hamas"},{"time":208470,"text":"cannot be understood without\nacknowledging the group's social work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212696,"text":"Now, this is a really complex picture,"},{"time":215094,"text":"yet in the West,\nwhen we look at armed groups,"},{"time":217595,"text":"we only think of the violent side."},{"time":219821,"text":"But that's not enough to understand\nthese groups' strength,"},{"time":222717,"text":"strategy or long-term vision."},{"time":225393,"text":"These groups are hybrid."},{"time":226977,"text":"They rise because they fill a gap\nleft by the government,"},{"time":230325,"text":"and they emerge\nto be both armed and political,"},{"time":233729,"text":"engage in violent struggle\nand provide governance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237431,"text":"And the more these organizations\nare complex and sophisticated,"},{"time":241463,"text":"the less we can think of them\nas the opposite of a state."},{"time":244828,"text":"Now, what do you call\na group like Hezbollah?"},{"time":247131,"text":"They run part of a territory,\nthey administer all their functions,"},{"time":250470,"text":"they pick up the garbage,\nthey run the sewage system."},{"time":253628,"text":"Is this a state? Is it a rebel group?"},{"time":256720,"text":"Or maybe something else,\nsomething different and new?"},{"time":260081,"text":"And what about ISIS?"},{"time":261786,"text":"The lines are blurred."},{"time":263080,"text":"We live in a world of states,\nnon-states, and in-between,"},{"time":266862,"text":"and the more states are weak,\nlike in the Middle East today,"},{"time":270299,"text":"the more non-state actors\nstep in and fill that gap."},{"time":273799,"text":"This matters for governments,\nbecause to counter these groups,"},{"time":276949,"text":"they will have to invest more\nin non-military tools."},{"time":281202,"text":"Filling that governance gap"},{"time":282697,"text":"has to be at the center\nof any sustainable approach."},{"time":286150,"text":"This also matters very much\nfor peacemaking and peacebuilding."},{"time":289813,"text":"If we better understand armed groups,"},{"time":291868,"text":"we will better know\nwhat incentives to offer"},{"time":294354,"text":"to encourage the transition\nfrom violence to nonviolence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298487,"text":"So in this new contest\nbetween states and non-states,"},{"time":302155,"text":"military power can win some battles,"},{"time":304831,"text":"but it will not give us\npeace nor stability."},{"time":308085,"text":"To achieve these objectives,"},{"time":309957,"text":"what we need is a long-term investment\nin filling that security gap,"},{"time":314786,"text":"in filling that governance gap"},{"time":316811,"text":"that allowed these groups\nto thrive in the first place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320220,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321395,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}